    "methodology": "Active Lives Survey measures activity over a rolling 28-day period using self-report questionnaire. The 150 minutes per week guideline derives from the UK Chief Medical Officers' physical activity guidelines (2019). Deprivation quintiles are assigned using the Index of Multiple Deprivation (2019) matched to survey respondent postcodes. Children's activity is measured against the CMO guideline of 60 minutes of moderate-to-vigorous physical activity per day. Walking and cycling rates are from the National Travel Survey and Active Lives combined.",
